# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# UAEDiscountHub — Amazon Creators API v3.2 Environment Variables
# Add these to your .env.local  (replace the old PAAPI vars)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── OLD PA-API vars (DELETE these — they no longer work) ─────────────────────
# AMAZON_PAAPI_ACCESS_KEY=...   ← DELETE
# AMAZON_PAAPI_SECRET_KEY=...   ← DELETE

# ── NEW Creators API v3.2 vars (from your CSV screenshot) ────────────────────
# Your Credential ID — the long string starting with amzn1.application-oa2-client.
AMAZON_CREDENTIAL_ID=amzn1.application-oa2-client.153a1...

# Your Credential Secret — the long string starting with amzn1.oa2-cs.v1.
AMAZON_CREDENTIAL_SECRET=amzn1.oa2-cs.v1.54750869c6f...

# Your Associates Partner Tag — from your CSV (Application Id column)
# Format shown in your CSV: uaediscounthu-21.uaediscc...
AMAZON_PARTNER_TAG=uaediscounthu-21

# ── Keep these (unchanged from before) ───────────────────────────────────────
CRON_SECRET=your_random_32char_secret_here
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# FILE LOCATIONS — where to put each new file in your project
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# lib/amazon/creators-api.ts     ← replaces lib/amazon/paapi.ts completely
# lib/amazon/sync.ts             ← same file, updated imports + config type
# app/api/amazon/sync/route.ts   ← same file, updated config type
# app/api/amazon/search/route.ts ← same file, updated imports
# app/api/amazon/import/route.ts ← same file, updated imports

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WHAT CHANGED IN YOUR CODE (summary for developer)
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. AUTH — completely different:
#    OLD: AWS4-HMAC-SHA256 signing with Access Key + Secret Key
#    NEW: OAuth 2.0 Bearer token from https://api.amazon.com/auth/o2/token
#         Token lasts 1 hour, cached automatically in module memory

# 2. CREDENTIALS:
#    OLD: AMAZON_PAAPI_ACCESS_KEY + AMAZON_PAAPI_SECRET_KEY
#    NEW: AMAZON_CREDENTIAL_ID + AMAZON_CREDENTIAL_SECRET  (from your CSV)

# 3. REQUEST FORMAT:
#    OLD: PascalCase  →  "ItemIds", "PartnerTag", "SearchIndex"
#    NEW: camelCase   →  "itemIds", "partnerTag", "searchIndex"

# 4. OFFERS DATA:
#    OLD: "Offers.Listings.Price"           (deprecated)
#    NEW: "offersV2.listings.price"         (better data, required for post Jan 2026)

# 5. RESPONSE KEYS:
#    OLD: item.ItemInfo.Title.DisplayValue
#    NEW: item.itemInfo.title.displayValue  (all camelCase)

# 6. ENDPOINT:
#    OLD: https://webservices.amazon.ae/paapi5/getitems  + AWS4 auth headers
#    NEW: https://webservices.amazon.ae/paapi5/getitems  + Bearer token header
#         (same URL path, different auth method!)

# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PARTNER TAG NOTE
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Your CSV shows Application Id as: uaediscounthu-21.uaediscc...
# The part BEFORE the first dot is your Associates tag: uaediscounthu-21
# This is what you put in partnerTag — NOT the full Application Id string

